  "time_ut": 1659443165,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dc4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd \u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d85\u0db1\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d91\u0dc3\u0dca.\u0da7\u0dd3.\u0d91\u0dc6\u0dca. 8 \u0d9a\u0dca \u0d87\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0ddd 7 \u0d9a\u0dca \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Polgahawela STF in a car accident. 8 maids and 7 in the hospital",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dewalegama Police say that 8 officers and 7 maids belonging to the Police Special Task Force were injured in a car accident on the Rambukkana-Polgahawela main road near the Narangbedda Police Special Task Force camp this morning (2nd).",
        "Dewalegama police said that eight persons including a sergeant working in Narangbedda camp and 7 officers working in Kurunegala camp are undergoing treatment in Kurunegala General Hospital and the maids of Agalum Institute are undergoing treatment in Kegalle General Hospital.",
        "The case related to the incident of damaging the Mawanella Buddha statues was held at the Sabaragamuwa Provincial Kegalle High Court yesterday. A group of officers belonging to the Kurunegala Police Special Task Force camp has arrived at the Rambukkana Narangbedda camp early in the morning to search the court premises where the case is taking place. A group of officers from Narangbedda camp had left at 6.00 am to provide security to the Kegalle High Court and then the Kurunegala group had traveled to Kegalle from Narangbedda at 7.00 am in a cab belonging to Narangbedda camp.",
        "The police said that a bus which was transporting a garment firm from Rambukkana to Polgahawela for official work came at a high speed and collided with the cab when it was about 500 meters towards Hirivadunna.",
        "Later, all the 8 Special Task Force officers in the cab got injured and were admitted to the Kurunegala General Hospital.",
        "7 maids of the bus have been admitted to Kegalle General Hospital with minor injuries and the driver of the bus is also undergoing treatment at Kegalle General Hospital."
      ],
